Create Report Page 2 - Zip Code Report

To allow the user to drill down further in detail per zip code, we want to create a new report page and call it Zip Code Report.
This report will showcase detailed information per zip code by using the following layout:

1. Top Left, using the same logo as previous page

2. Top middle, Title with a dynamic card showcasing current Zip Code

3. Top Right, year slicer

4. Back button to the first report page which we will do in the next step (5)

5. Crime Location - Map

6. Case Number, Domestic or Not - Pie Chart

7. Case Numbers by Type of Crime - Bar Chart

 8. Crimes Compared to Average - KPI

9. Arrests True compared to Average - KPI

10. Case Number, Arrest or Not - Pie Chart

11. Case Numbers by Year - Area Chart


2. Top middle, Title with a dynamic card showcasing current Zip Code

    a) Add a card from the visualizations


    b) Add Zip Code to Fields

This card will only showcase 1 zip code once we add drill-through functionality as it will add a filter for this chosen zip code. We will complete this card in the final step.


3. Top Right, year slicer

    a) Add a slicer from visualizations and add Year to Fields



5. Crime Location - Map

    a) Add a map from visualizations


    b) Add Latitude and Longitude. Power BI will automatically aggregate to average, so change it to "Don't summarize"


    c) Format the map by changing the title and title color, font and size


    d) Note that the map will utilize the drill-through zip code filter and zoom in on that area. We will add drill-through in the next step (5).


6. Case Number, Domestic or Not - Pie Chart

    a) Add a Pie Chart from Visualization


    b) Add Domestic in Legend. Add Case Number in Values and make sure its aggregated to count.


    c) Format the chart by changing chart color and title to fit to the report design


7. Case Numbers by Type of Crime - Bar Chart

    a) Add a Stacked Bar Chart from Visualizations


    b) Add Primary Type to Axis and Case Number to Value. Make sure Case Number is aggregated to Count.


    c) Format the bar color as well as title



 8. Crimes Compared to Average - KPI

    a) Add a KPI from Visualizations

    b) Add ID to Indicator, Year to Trend axis and Crime Avg to Target goals

    c) Format the title and make the chart less tall to fit another KPI


9. Arrests True compared to Average - KPI

    a) Add a KPI from Visualizations

    b) Add Arrests True to Indicator, Year to Trend axis and Arrests True Avg to Target goals


    c)Format the title



10. Case Number, Arrest or Not - Pie Chart

    a) Add a Pie Chart from Visualizations

    b) Add Arrest to Legend and Arrest to Values. Make sure Values is aggregated to count.


    c) Format the chart by changing chart color and title to fit to the report design



11. Case Numbers by Year - Area Chart

    a) Add Area Chart from Visualization

    b) Add Year to Axis and Case Number to Values. Make sure Values is aggregated to count.


    c) Format chart color and title
